OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5F'We are waiting for rain,  
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Ffor winter, for God'       
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Herve Trentin, a 34-year veteran of the
OL,6, Gironde fire department, stood on the  
OL,7, edge of a charred section of forest    
OL,8, wiping tears from his cheeks. It was   
OL,9, the second time Trentin had cried that 
OL,10, morning.                               
OL,12,F"I'm sorry," he said, composing        
OL,13,Fhimself. "This is our forest. It is    
OL,14,Fheart-breaking to watch it burn."      
OL,16,FTrentin and his small team were moving 
OL,17,Faround an area south of the French city
OL,18,Fof Bordeaux, in the Gironde region, on 
OL,19,FSaturday morning, trying to stay ahead 
OL,20,Fof a megafire.                         
